Floyd Mayweather Jnr continued his preparations for his fight with Manny Pacquiao in May on day two of his official training camp in Las Vegas.

The undefeated welterweight champion kept fans updated of his progress with a series of pictures uploaded to social media website Shots.

Mayweather, who currently holds the WBC, WBA and Ring titles, shared snaps from within the gym as he was put through a rigorous pad workout by his trainer.

